      "note_no": "158",
      "note": "Some of the commentators (e.g., Razi) interpret the phrase huwa khadi uhum (lit., \"He is their deceiver\") as \"He will requite them for their deception\". However, the rendering adopted by me seems to be more in tune with 2:9, where the same type of hypocrisy is spoken of: \"They would deceive God and those who have attained to faith - the while they deceive none but themselves, and are not aware of it.\" See also Manar V, 469 f., where both these interpretations are considered to be mutually complementary."
